62
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,586
- Now? You mean tonight?

63
00:05:01,586 --> 00:05:02,517
- Yes.

64
00:05:02,517 --> 00:05:03,862
- It's pretty late.

65
00:05:03,862 --> 00:05:05,551
- Yeah, I know what
 time it is, mother.

66
00:05:05,551 --> 00:05:06,551
- James, you don't sound good.

67
00:05:06,551 --> 00:05:08,034
Are you all right?

68
00:05:09,344 --> 00:05:12,000
- Would it be all
 right if I came by?

69
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,103
- Absolutely.

70
00:05:18,793 --> 00:05:21,413
- Sorry about the hour.

71
00:05:21,413 --> 00:05:22,862
- Don't be silly.

72
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:32,206
Should I ask, or should I wait?

73
00:05:34,034 --> 00:05:35,551
- Donald has AIDS.

74
00:05:37,517 --> 00:05:38,758
He's gonna die soon,

75
00:05:38,758 --> 00:05:39,689
so it would mean
 a great deal to me

76
00:05:39,689 --> 00:05:41,896
if you don't get hysterical.

77
00:05:44,586 --> 00:05:47,172
- How long have you known?

78
00:05:47,172 --> 00:05:50,758
- He tested positive
 two years ago.

79
00:05:50,758 --> 00:05:53,862
- And you're telling me now?

80
00:05:53,862 --> 00:05:56,137
- I had to hospitalize
 him this morning.

81
00:05:56,137 --> 00:05:58,275
The KS has become very severe.

82
00:05:58,275 --> 00:05:59,482
- The what?

83
00:05:59,482 --> 00:06:03,482
- Kaposi sarcoma,
 it's a kind of cancer.

84
00:06:03,482 --> 00:06:06,724
He wanted to be at
 home, but I couldn't.

85
00:06:06,724 --> 00:06:09,655
It'll be better for
 him in the hospital.

86
00:06:09,655 --> 00:06:11,448
- He hasn't even
 looked ill lately.

87
00:06:11,448 --> 00:06:12,275
I mean--

88
00:06:12,275 --> 00:06:13,482
- Lately?

89
00:06:13,482 --> 00:06:14,689
