Roses usually say,

104
00:06:51,379 --> 00:06:52,448
and candy.

105
00:06:52,448 --> 00:06:54,000
Does he like candy?

106
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,448
- He has a tremendous
 sweet tooth,

107
00:06:55,448 --> 00:06:59,931
I sometimes I have to be very
 stern with him about that.

108
00:07:02,689 --> 00:07:05,034
- Well I haven't had to deal
 with this since your father.

109
00:07:05,034 --> 00:07:06,482
- Deal with what?

110
00:07:08,206 --> 00:07:09,034
With what?

111
00:07:10,103 --> 00:07:10,965
- Dying.

112
00:07:12,862 --> 00:07:14,482
- Donald and I have
 been to 14 funerals

113
00:07:14,482 --> 00:07:16,310
in the past 18 months.

114
00:07:21,931 --> 00:07:22,758
[phone ringing]

115
00:07:22,758 --> 00:07:23,896
Look who's here.

116
00:07:23,896 --> 00:07:26,413
- Everybody comes to Rick.

117
00:07:26,413 --> 00:07:27,413
- Hi Donald.

118
00:07:28,551 --> 00:07:30,413
- The long one
 has to be flowers.

119
00:07:30,413 --> 00:07:31,758
- He's so quick.

120
00:07:33,586 --> 00:07:36,137
- If this is candy
 it's our secret.

121
00:07:36,137 --> 00:07:39,241
- The secret is out, and
it's not on the menu.

122
00:07:39,241 --> 00:07:43,068
- See, things are already
 taking an ugly turn.

123
00:07:49,689 --> 00:07:51,655
I'm dying for a cigarette.

124
00:07:51,655 --> 00:07:52,724
- Have one.

125
00:07:52,724 --> 00:07:54,068
- [James] He gave it up.

126
00:07:54,068 --> 00:07:56,310
- Me too, three months ago.

127
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:57,827
- It's hell, isn't it?

128
00:07:57,827 --> 00:08:01,931
- Oh, I can't be held
 responsible for my actions.

129
00:08:01,931 --> 00:08:05,310
- I gave up smoking
 for my health.

130
00:08:05,310 --> 00:08:07,000
The insurance company
 should come up

131
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,793
with a whole new concept,

132
00:08:09,793 --> 00:08:11,103
irony insurance.

133
00:08:12,896 --> 00:08:16,206
I tell you there's a
 fortune to be made.

134
00:08:17,724 --> 00:08:19,724
Remember when we smoked?

135
00:08:23,724 --> 00:08:25,758
- Does he have any family?

136
00:08:25,758 --> 00:08:27,413
- His mother.

137
00:08:27,413 --> 00:08:30,551
His father's been lost
 in the mist of time.

138
00:08:30,551 --> 00:08:33,103
- I assume that she
 knew before I did.

139
00:08:33,103 --> 00:08:34,344
- Knew what?

140
00:08:34,344 --> 00:08:37,103
- About Donald,
 what's happening.

141
00:08:37,103 --> 00:08:39,689
- Donald and his mother
 haven't spoken for years.

142
00:08:39,689 --> 00:08:41,172
- Why not?

143
00:08:41,172 --> 00:08:42,931
- Her response to his
 sexual orientation

144
00:08:42,931 --> 00:08:44,827
was less than enlightened.

145
00:08:44,827 --> 00:08:46,896
- I gather you're
 understating it?

146
00:08:46,896 --> 00:08:48,172
- Considerably.

147
00:08:48,172 --> 00:08:50,275
- Well, she should be told,

148
00:08:50,275 --> 00:08:51,931
about Donald, what's happening.

149
00:08:51,931 --> 00:08:53,275
- Mother try to stop
saying that, would you?

150
00:08:53,275 --> 00:08:54,689
About Donald, what's happening.

151
00:08:54,689 --> 00:08:56,448
Donald has AIDS, he's dying,

152
00:08:56,448 --> 00:08:58,793
can we please stop
 tap dancing, finally?

153
00:08:58,793 --> 00:08:59,620
- What's going on?

154
00:08:59,620 --> 00:09:00,758
Why are you so angry?

155
00:09:00,758 --> 00:09:02,482
What tap dancing?

156
00:09:02,482 --> 00:09:04,068
- Sorry.

157
00:09:04,068 --> 00:09:05,344
I'm a little stressed.

158
00:09:05,344 --> 00:09:07,137
I haven't slept in days.

159
00:09:07,137 --> 00:09:09,172
