217
00:12:50,068 --> 00:12:53,758
Do you have a pack of butts
 tucked away in your bag, too?

218
00:12:53,758 --> 00:12:56,758
- James used to teeth on
that when he was a baby.

219
00:12:56,758 --> 00:12:58,413
See, there are his teeth marks.

220
00:12:58,413 --> 00:12:59,827
- If you don't mind I'm
 not gonna get sentimental

221
00:12:59,827 --> 00:13:02,965
about something that was
lighting the way to your grave.

222
00:13:02,965 --> 00:13:05,620
[phone ringing]

223
00:13:15,172 --> 00:13:17,758
[phone ringing]

224
00:13:17,758 --> 00:13:18,586
- Yeah?

225
00:13:19,689 --> 00:13:20,517
Hello?

226
00:13:22,068 --> 00:13:23,896
When the heavy breathing
starts you're canceled,

227
00:13:23,896 --> 00:13:26,310
you got three seconds.

228
00:13:26,310 --> 00:13:27,344
- Hello.

229
00:13:27,344 --> 00:13:29,482
Am I speaking to Missus Barnes?

230
00:13:29,482 --> 00:13:30,793
Luanne Barnes?

231
00:13:30,793 --> 00:13:31,827
- That's who you're speaking to,

232
00:13:31,827 --> 00:13:33,551
who's speaking to me?

233
00:13:37,586 --> 00:13:39,931
[dial tone]

234
00:13:54,586 --> 00:13:57,034
[siren on TV]

235
00:14:17,793 --> 00:14:20,586
- I wonder if I've given you
 the wrong impression tonight.

236
00:14:20,586 --> 00:14:21,862
I hope you don't think
 this is the first time

237
00:14:21,862 --> 00:14:23,793
I've ever thought about it.

238
00:14:23,793 --> 00:14:26,620
I mean, what's
 happened to Donald.

239
00:14:27,862 --> 00:14:29,620
How could I not think about it?

240
00:14:29,620 --> 00:14:31,758
For years now, ever since
 we all first heard about it,

241
00:14:31,758 --> 00:14:35,137
I wanted to say something
 to James, but I never did.

242
00:14:35,137 --> 00:14:36,068
I couldn't.

243
00:14:37,241 --> 00:14:40,310
I was too scared to
 get the words out.

244
00:14:40,310 --> 00:14:42,862
- Is that why you're not
telling me about James?

245
00:14:42,862 --> 00:14:44,448
- Telling you what?

246
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,137
- Is he all right, Audrey?

247
00:14:49,034 --> 00:14:51,310
Or does he have it too?

248
00:14:51,310 --> 00:14:54,758
- Well of course he's all right.

249
00:14:54,758 --> 00:14:57,758
I'm sure he is, he must be.

250
00:14:57,758 --> 00:14:59,137
- You don't know?

251
00:15:00,517 --> 00:15:01,758
- Harry, if he wasn't all right,

252
00:15:01,758 --> 00:15:05,172
he would have told
 me, wouldn't he?

253
00:15:05,172 --> 00:15:06,793
Yes, he would have.

254
00:15:08,172 --> 00:15:10,310
- You didn't ask?

255
00:15:10,310 --> 00:15:13,206
[soft piano music]

256
00:16:32,068 --> 00:16:33,068
- You hung up?

257
00:16:33,068 --> 00:16:35,379
Why did you hang up?

258
00:16:35,379 --> 00:16:38,068
- Because I realized the
 instant I heard her voice

259
00:16:38,068 --> 00:16:39,931
there would be no point in it,

260
00:16:39,931 --> 00:16:43,206
when I told her who I was,
 and why I was calling.

261
00:16:43,206 --> 00:16:45,275
This is a woman for
 whom homosexuality

262
00:16:45,275 --> 00:16:48,068
is an offense against
 God, man, and nature.

263
00:16:48,068 --> 00:16:50,241
- Well, write her a letter.

264
00:16:50,241 --> 00:16:52,586
Send her a wire,
 she should be told.

265
00:16:52,586 --> 00:16:55,551
Let her make up her own mind
 what she wants to do about it.

266
00:16:55,551 --> 00:16:57,172
It would be hurtful for
 Donald if she doesn't come,

267
00:16:57,172 --> 00:16:59,448
but I think it's a
chance you have to take.

