526
00:28:37,620 --> 00:28:40,206
- He's gonna die
 you stupid bitch.

527
00:28:40,206 --> 00:28:42,034
- Well if he wasn't what he is,

528
00:28:42,034 --> 00:28:44,482
he wouldn't be gonna
 die now would he?

529
00:28:44,482 --> 00:28:46,034
Would he?

530
00:28:46,034 --> 00:28:47,689
I hated what he is.

531
00:28:47,689 --> 00:28:49,379
It turns my stomach.

532
00:28:49,379 --> 00:28:50,379
You here me?

533
00:28:54,241 --> 00:28:56,241
- Get me out of here.

534
00:28:56,241 --> 00:28:58,310
Get me out of here quick.

535
00:29:00,172 --> 00:29:02,551
[crowd talking]

536
00:29:02,551 --> 00:29:05,034
[dog barking]

537
00:29:08,344 --> 00:29:10,965
[horn honking]

538
00:29:29,896 --> 00:29:32,379
- By the by, how did Mom cope?

539
00:29:36,034 --> 00:29:37,034
Your mother?

540
00:29:38,172 --> 00:29:41,206
Audrey, how did she
survive her face-to-face

541
00:29:41,206 --> 00:29:44,862
confront with the grim
 reaper the other day?

542
00:29:44,862 --> 00:29:48,034
- She saw right through
 your flimsy tissue of wit,

543
00:29:48,034 --> 00:29:49,931
admired amongst us.

544
00:29:49,931 --> 00:29:52,965
- I thought she met them
all really well for her.

545
00:29:52,965 --> 00:29:55,103
She seemed quite fearless.

546
00:29:56,275 --> 00:29:57,172
- Gin.

547
00:29:57,172 --> 00:29:58,793
- What?

548
00:29:58,793 --> 00:30:00,517
No mercy, even now?

549
00:30:00,517 --> 00:30:01,482
[toilet flushing]

550
00:30:01,482 --> 00:30:03,655
- See you later, Donald.

551
00:30:03,655 --> 00:30:07,586
- Your hair is like a
field of silver daisies.

552
00:30:07,586 --> 00:30:11,137
I'd like to run barefoot
through your hair.

553
00:30:13,724 --> 00:30:17,206
They don't write movies
like that anymore.

554
00:30:18,793 --> 00:30:20,137
Mother for mother, I'd say mine

555
00:30:20,137 --> 00:30:23,551
has the better
 bargain of the two.

556
00:30:23,551 --> 00:30:27,344
One more hand, but
 only if I can cheat.

557
00:30:27,344 --> 00:30:29,344
- What better bargain?

558
00:30:29,344 --> 00:30:31,793
- To be spared all this dreck,

559
00:30:31,793 --> 00:30:34,448
blissful ignorance and all that.

560
00:30:35,862 --> 00:30:37,965
- How can you be so
 certain she'd want to be?

561
00:30:37,965 --> 00:30:40,068
- James, don't be a dunce.

562
00:30:41,655 --> 00:30:42,931
Who wouldn't want to be?

563
00:30:42,931 --> 00:30:45,862
Would you choose this
 if you had a choice?

564
00:30:45,862 --> 00:30:46,931
Would Audrey?

565
00:30:51,896 --> 00:30:52,689
I'm sorry.

566
00:30:55,344 --> 00:30:59,689
It's becoming time for
 another controlled substance,

567
00:30:59,689 --> 00:31:03,862
something by way of a mood
 elevator would be nice.

568
00:31:05,551 --> 00:31:07,000
- Here.

569
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:09,379
You want me to get the nurse?

570
00:31:11,620 --> 00:31:13,965
- I'll be brave if you will.

571
00:31:26,965 --> 00:31:28,724
When are you gonna be?

572
00:31:28,724 --> 00:31:29,551
- What?

573
00:31:30,724 --> 00:31:33,517
- Not brave, wrong
 word of course.

574
00:31:36,448 --> 00:31:37,275
Sensible.

575
00:31:38,827 --> 00:31:40,827
When are you gonna be sensible?

576
00:31:40,827 --> 00:31:43,724
- I thought you promised
 not to bring that up again.

577
00:31:43,724 --> 00:31:44,517
- I lied.

578
00:31:46,275 --> 00:31:47,310
Please James,

579
00:31:48,655 --> 00:31:52,000
it just isn't rational
 not to be tested.

580
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:53,517
- If I promise to do it,
will you leave it alone?

581
00:31:53,517 --> 00:31:54,310
- Yeah.

582
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:01,724
Could be negative, James.

583
00:32:01,724 --> 00:32:03,620
- Shall we calculate the
astronomical odds against that?

584
00:32:03,620 --> 00:32:05,344
Let's find the nearest computer.

585
00:32:05,344 --> 00:32:06,827
- Michael Roby
 died two years ago,

586
00:32:06,827 --> 00:32:08,275
and Peter is still
 testing negative.

587
00:32:08,275 --> 00:32:09,689
- Peter wants to know, Donald.

588
00:32:09,689 --> 00:32:11,551
- Yes, and if God forbid
he does go positive,

589
00:32:11,551 --> 00:32:12,793
at least he'll have the earliest

590
00:32:12,793 --> 00:32:15,103
treatment possible, won't he?

591
00:32:15,103 --> 00:32:17,413
As I might have had when I
 was still in the denial mode

592
00:32:17,413 --> 00:32:19,068
of me, it can't happen to me.

593
00:32:19,068 --> 00:32:21,896
- It's my choice, Donald.

594
00:32:21,896 --> 00:32:22,724
Mine.

595
00:32:30,689 --> 00:32:33,241
- I think I'm gonna win,

596
00:32:33,241 --> 00:32:36,172
and I haven't
 started cheating yet.

597
00:32:39,413 --> 00:32:41,655
- I gave it my best
 hon, really I did.

598
00:32:41,655 --> 00:32:43,206
- [James] Mission impossible.

599
00:32:43,206 --> 00:32:46,137
- She's one of those,
it's-God's-curse people.

600
00:32:46,137 --> 00:32:47,000
- Oh yeah.

601
00:32:48,206 --> 00:32:50,275
Thank you for trying
 Mother, I mean that.

602
00:32:50,275 --> 00:32:51,137
- You're welcome.

603
00:32:51,137 --> 00:32:52,448
I hate her guts.

604
00:32:53,827 --> 00:32:56,206
- It's a new chapter
 for your memoirs.

605
00:32:56,206 --> 00:32:57,413
Come home.

606
00:32:57,413 --> 00:32:58,965
- You know what's gonna
happen, don't you?

607
00:32:58,965 --> 00:33:01,206
On the plane tomorrow I'll
think of exactly the magic words

608
00:33:01,206 --> 00:33:03,793
I could have used, that
 would have had her with me.

609
00:33:03,793 --> 00:33:06,413
- No you won't,
 there aren't any.

610
00:33:06,413 --> 00:33:09,068
[country music]

611
00:33:12,206 --> 00:33:14,586
- Come on Lu, give us
 a break, who was she?

612
00:33:14,586 --> 00:33:15,862
- None of your business.

613
00:33:15,862 --> 00:33:18,241
- It's all gonna come
 out sooner or later.

614
00:33:18,241 --> 00:33:20,689
I'm guessing some old rich uncle

615
00:33:20,689 --> 00:33:22,689
you didn't know you
 had bought the farm,

616
00:33:22,689 --> 00:33:24,965
and left you a fortune.

617
00:33:24,965 --> 00:33:25,793
- Be real.

618
00:33:26,724 --> 00:33:28,965
- Wish I'd been there.

619
00:33:28,965 --> 00:33:30,413
The way I heard it,

620
00:33:30,413 --> 00:33:34,103
we're talking lifestyles
 of the rich and disgusting.

621
00:33:34,103 --> 00:33:36,379
- Come on Lu, spill it.

622
00:33:36,379 --> 00:33:39,620
- Okay, okay, I won
 a contest all right?

623
00:33:39,620 --> 00:33:40,448
- No kidding?

624
00:33:40,448 --> 00:33:41,689
- No.

625
00:33:41,689 --> 00:33:42,344
- Well now we're
 getting somewhere.

626
00:33:42,344 --> 00:33:43,172
What contest?

627
00:33:44,689 --> 00:33:46,413
- Mother of the year.

628
00:33:50,689 --> 00:33:52,862
[thunder]

629
00:34:11,344 --> 00:34:13,517
[raining]

630
00:34:47,724 --> 00:34:51,206
[sentimental flute music]

631
00:35:36,068 --> 00:35:38,758
[phone ringing]

632
00:35:46,517 --> 00:35:47,344
- Yes.

633
00:35:48,689 --> 00:35:49,517
Hello?

634
00:35:51,758 --> 00:35:52,586
Hello?

635
00:35:54,310 --> 00:35:56,379
- Is he really gonna die?

636
00:36:37,172 --> 00:36:39,344
- I admire you a lot for this.

637
00:36:39,344 --> 00:36:41,172
- I'm not doing
 this to be admired.

638
00:36:41,172 --> 00:36:42,896
- I know that.

639
00:36:42,896 --> 00:36:45,724
- I'm honestly not
 sure why I'm doing it.

640
00:36:45,724 --> 00:36:48,206
- Well, maybe you'll find out.

641
00:36:50,310 --> 00:36:51,551
- I generally like to have

642
00:36:51,551 --> 00:36:55,000
the finding out part
 of things before.

643
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:58,000
It's easier with less of
 the why-did-I-do-its after.

644
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:00,310
Too many why-did-I-do-its
 tend to get you down,

645
00:37:00,310 --> 00:37:02,068
you know what I mean?

646
00:37:03,448 --> 00:37:05,551
- How soon can you leave?

647
00:37:07,103 --> 00:37:09,068
- Well, got a boss
 to tell I won't be in

648
00:37:09,068 --> 00:37:12,000
for a couple of days,
 throw some stuff together.

649
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:15,137
Aside from that,
anytime I guess.

650
00:37:15,137 --> 00:37:16,413
- Well, there's plenty of time,

651
00:37:16,413 --> 00:37:19,620
the plane doesn't
 leave until 6:30.

652
00:37:19,620 --> 00:37:21,310
- What plane?

653
00:37:21,310 --> 00:37:22,241
- To Little Rock,

654
00:37:22,241 --> 00:37:23,206
there's a short layover there

655
00:37:23,206 --> 00:37:24,724
to change planes for San Diego.

656
00:37:24,724 --> 00:37:27,137
- Change what planes?

657
00:37:27,137 --> 00:37:29,517
- Well we have to fly
 from here to Little Rock,

658
00:37:29,517 --> 00:37:31,655
on this little commuter airline.

659
00:37:31,655 --> 00:37:33,172
- You mean you
 didn't come direct?

660
00:37:33,172 --> 00:37:34,103
- From San Diego?

661
00:37:34,103 --> 00:37:34,965
- Yeah.

662
00:37:34,965 --> 00:37:36,413
- No.

663
00:37:36,413 --> 00:37:39,413
There are no direct flights
from San Diego to Fayetteville.

664
00:37:39,413 --> 00:37:42,310
But it's a quick trip
 from here to Little Rock.

665
00:37:42,310 --> 00:37:45,034
- Oh yeah, I took a quick trip

666
00:37:45,034 --> 00:37:46,689
on one of their airplanes once.

667
00:37:46,689 --> 00:37:49,275
Lasted about half a minute.

668
00:37:49,275 --> 00:37:51,413
- [Audrey] What do you mean?

669
00:37:51,413 --> 00:37:54,793
- The propeller stopped turning.

670
00:37:54,793 --> 00:37:56,137
- What happened?

671
00:37:56,137 --> 00:37:58,310
- What happened is
 the plane crashed.

672
00:37:58,310 --> 00:38:00,206
The wings don't flap you know.

673
00:38:00,206 --> 00:38:02,310
- My God, were you badly hurt?

674
00:38:02,310 --> 00:38:03,655
- Broke my knee.

675
00:38:05,206 --> 00:38:07,310
Two people killed though.

676
00:38:08,482 --> 00:38:10,241
I'll be driving.

677
00:38:10,241 --> 00:38:11,517
- I beg your pardon?

678
00:38:11,517 --> 00:38:15,000
- To Little Rock,
 meet you there.

679
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,655
- Driving?

680
00:38:16,655 --> 00:38:17,482
- Yeah.

681
00:38:19,793 --> 00:38:21,793
- You won't fly?

682
00:38:21,793 --> 00:38:23,275
- On one of them little things?

683
00:38:23,275 --> 00:38:24,586
No way.

684
00:38:24,586 --> 00:38:26,068
- Do you know what the odds are

685
00:38:26,068 --> 00:38:28,758
against your ever being in
 an accident like that again?

686
00:38:28,758 --> 00:38:29,965
If you live to be 200.

687
00:38:29,965 --> 00:38:32,000
- I'll tell you what
 it's about lady.

688
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:34,137
Being laid up in bed
 scared cross-eyed

689
00:38:34,137 --> 00:38:36,413
for about a week after
 is what it's about.

690
00:38:36,413 --> 00:38:38,655
Waking up in sweats, three
 or four times a year,

691
00:38:38,655 --> 00:38:41,344
to the present day,
that's what it's about.

692
00:38:41,344 --> 00:38:42,862
I'm not flying in
 nothin' that has less

693
00:38:42,862 --> 00:38:46,931
than three or four
 humongous jet motors.

694
00:38:46,931 --> 00:38:48,482
Get one of them to
 make a little detour

695
00:38:48,482 --> 00:38:51,724
to Fayetteville
 Airport, no problem.

696
00:38:51,724 --> 00:38:54,344
- I don't think I
 could arrange that.

697
00:38:54,344 --> 00:38:56,517
- Meet you in Little Rock.

698
00:38:59,379 --> 00:39:00,965
- Wait.

699
00:39:00,965 --> 00:39:03,000
How long is the
 drive to Little Rock?

700
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:04,586
- About four hours.

701
00:39:05,793 --> 00:39:08,448
- I'd really rather
 we went together.

702
00:39:08,448 --> 00:39:11,586
- Why, afraid I
 might change my mind?

703
00:39:11,586 --> 00:39:12,758
- Can you honestly tell me

704
00:39:12,758 --> 00:39:14,275
I don't have to
 concerned about that?

705
00:39:14,275 --> 00:39:16,724
Look, I don't know
you, you don't know me,

706
00:39:16,724 --> 00:39:19,206
but I do know how hard
 this is for you to do.

707
00:39:19,206 --> 00:39:22,103
And I know that part of you
 still doesn't want to do it.

708
00:39:22,103 --> 00:39:23,310
- You sure know a hell of a lot

709
00:39:23,310 --> 00:39:25,482
for somebody that don't
know me, don't you?

710
00:39:25,482 --> 00:39:27,034
- Oh for God's sake how
 could I have sat with you

711
00:39:27,034 --> 00:39:29,275
yesterday in that trailer
 and listened to you

712
00:39:29,275 --> 00:39:30,689
and not know that?

713
00:39:30,689 --> 00:39:32,000
Maybe you could
 use some help to do

714
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:34,862
what I think you
most want to do.

715
00:39:34,862 --> 00:39:38,724
Four hours can be an awfully
 long time to go without help.

716
00:39:38,724 --> 00:39:42,482
- I'm not flying to
 Little Rock, case closed.

717
00:39:42,482 --> 00:39:43,655
- No you're not.

718
00:39:43,655 --> 00:39:46,068
We're driving to
 Little Rock, together.

719
00:39:46,068 --> 00:39:49,310
- It's a pretty
 drive, right now.

720
00:39:49,310 --> 00:39:53,172
Just tell me where you
want me to pick you up.

721
00:39:53,172 --> 00:39:55,344
- Does this have
 air conditioning?

722
00:39:55,344 --> 00:39:59,000
- No, but it has windows
that you roll down.

723
00:40:01,586 --> 00:40:03,413
- I have a suggestion.

724
00:40:04,517 --> 00:40:05,724
Well I can't guarantee
 anything James,

725
00:40:05,724 --> 00:40:08,034
this is strictly
 one step at a time.

726
00:40:08,034 --> 00:40:11,000
She's a tough hombre, I feel
 like I'm walking on eggs.

727
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:12,586
How's Donald?

728
00:40:12,586 --> 00:40:14,172
- A bit of an
 upswing this morning.

729
00:40:14,172 --> 00:40:15,827
- [Audrey] Is that good?

730
00:40:15,827 --> 00:40:17,379
- What goes up.

731
00:40:17,379 --> 00:40:18,551
- Well, okay.

732
00:40:18,551 --> 00:40:20,172
Look, as of this moment,
we're on our way.

733
00:40:20,172 --> 00:40:21,862
We'll be in San Diego tonight.

734
00:40:21,862 --> 00:40:23,586
I almost had to drive
 with her in her car

735
00:40:23,586 --> 00:40:24,965
all the way to Little Rock.

736
00:40:24,965 --> 00:40:27,103
Looks like a discard
 from Rent a Wreck.

737
00:40:27,103 --> 00:40:28,344
- Not a pretty picture,

738
00:40:28,344 --> 00:40:30,241
I assume you made
 other arrangements.

739
00:40:30,241 --> 00:40:32,827
[fiddle music]

740
00:40:58,931 --> 00:41:01,068
- Okay, we're out of here.

741
00:41:14,862 --> 00:41:17,413
[car starting]

742
00:41:46,689 --> 00:41:47,724
- No, thanks.

743
00:41:54,379 --> 00:41:57,000
- Doesn't that ruin the air
conditioning, putting that down?

744
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:58,103
- It's just while
 you're smoking.

745
00:41:58,103 --> 00:41:59,344
I used to do that.

746
00:41:59,344 --> 00:42:00,896
I don't want to get re-hooked.

747
00:42:00,896 --> 00:42:03,310
It's a daily threat at best.

748
00:42:03,310 --> 00:42:04,551
- Is it gonna be a problem?

749
00:42:04,551 --> 00:42:07,310
- No, go right
 ahead, no problem.

750
00:42:10,827 --> 00:42:13,137
- I've never been in a
 car like this before.

751
00:42:13,137 --> 00:42:16,034
I guess you figured that out.

752
00:42:16,034 --> 00:42:17,862
I'd really love to
 hear that radio,

753
00:42:17,862 --> 00:42:19,862
if I could just find it.

754
00:42:25,586 --> 00:42:28,241
[country music]

755
00:42:39,344 --> 00:42:42,724
- I have to find a place
 to stay when we get there.

756
00:42:42,724 --> 00:42:44,137
- It's all taken care of.

757
00:42:44,137 --> 00:42:46,034
We booked you a hotel room.

758
00:42:46,034 --> 00:42:47,413
- Hope it's in my budget.

759
00:42:47,413 --> 00:42:48,241
- You don't have to
 think about that,

760
00:42:48,241 --> 00:42:50,379
it's all taken care of.

761
00:42:50,379 --> 00:42:54,241
- I don't need it to
 be all taken care of.

762
00:42:54,241 --> 00:42:55,034
- Okay.

763
00:42:57,724 --> 00:43:00,206
How'd it go with your boss
 getting some time off?

764
00:43:00,206 --> 00:43:01,448
- Fine.

765
00:43:01,448 --> 00:43:04,241
I was a bit shifty
 about how long.

766
00:43:05,241 --> 00:43:07,724
What kind of time does he have?

767
00:43:07,724 --> 00:43:08,965
- It's hard to say.

768
00:43:08,965 --> 00:43:11,000
- [Luanne] Not long?

769
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:12,620
- A week,

770
00:43:12,620 --> 00:43:13,448
maybe two.

771
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:21,137
- I haven't seen
him in 11 years.

772
00:43:21,137 --> 00:43:23,827
He was 17 when I kicked him out.

773
00:43:25,310 --> 00:43:27,379
- Do you have any
 other children?

774
00:43:27,379 --> 00:43:31,206
- Yeah, I have two daughters
 from my second marriage.

775
00:43:31,206 --> 00:43:34,034
One lives in Ohio,
 one's in Florida,

776
00:43:34,034 --> 00:43:36,379
we get together on holidays.

777
00:43:38,551 --> 00:43:40,896
- So, you English, huh?

778
00:43:40,896 --> 00:43:41,724
- Yes.

779
00:43:42,689 --> 00:43:44,586
- Your son is, too?

780
00:43:44,586 --> 00:43:46,965
- He was born here.

781
00:43:46,965 --> 00:43:49,448
- I never met anybody English.

782
00:43:51,448 --> 00:43:53,172
How about a pit stop?

783
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:57,655
How'd you find out
 what your kid was?

784
00:43:57,655 --> 00:43:59,689
I found out by asking,
 how'd you find out?

785
00:43:59,689 --> 00:44:00,724
- He told me.

786
