 your pretty lips, huh?

1046
00:56:51,275 --> 00:56:52,517
- Never.

1047
00:56:52,517 --> 00:56:55,517
- Not even before you
knew what your son was?

1048
00:56:55,517 --> 00:56:57,000
- Oh come on.

1049
00:56:57,000 --> 00:56:58,551
Everybody uses ignorant
 words when they're young,

1050
00:56:58,551 --> 00:57:00,241
and don't know any better.

1051
00:57:00,241 --> 00:57:03,448
But some of us grow
 up, and know better.

1052
00:57:03,448 --> 00:57:06,448
- And some of us grow up
 and stay ignorant, right?

1053
00:57:06,448 --> 00:57:07,655
- I'm not trying to insult you,

1054
00:57:07,655 --> 00:57:09,551
stop putting words
 into my mouth.

1055
00:57:09,551 --> 00:57:12,034
- Maybe there's some
 already in it, lady.

1056
00:57:12,034 --> 00:57:14,655
- You just cannot believe
 that I am not like you.

1057
00:57:14,655 --> 00:57:16,965
You want me to be like you.

1058
00:57:16,965 --> 00:57:18,448
Well, I'm not.

1059
00:57:18,448 --> 00:57:19,275
- Like me?

1060
00:57:20,551 --> 00:57:22,206
What do you mean, like me?

1061
00:57:22,206 --> 00:57:25,379
I got a son dying from what
 he is, and so could yours.

1062
00:57:25,379 --> 00:57:27,275
I just wanted
 Donnie to be normal.

1063
00:57:27,275 --> 00:57:29,344
I would have had a
 son all these years.

1064
00:57:29,344 --> 00:57:30,275
That's all I wanted.

1065
00:57:30,275 --> 00:57:32,275
- You had a son all these years.

1066
00:57:32,275 --> 00:57:33,862
- One I could love.

1067
00:57:33,862 --> 00:57:35,448
- You could have
 loved him anyway.

1068
00:57:35,448 --> 00:57:36,482
- Like you love yours, huh?

1069
00:57:36,482 --> 00:57:37,862
- [Audrey] Yes.

1070
00:57:37,862 --> 00:57:39,034
- Anyway?

1071
00:57:39,034 --> 00:57:41,000
You mean, in spite
 of what he is?

1072
00:57:41,000 --> 00:57:41,965
That how you loved yours?

1073
00:57:41,965 --> 00:57:42,827
- Oh stop.

1074
00:57:42,827 --> 00:57:44,379
- Oh come on.

1075
00:57:44,379 --> 00:57:46,482
Get the hell out of here.

1076
00:57:52,000 --> 00:57:55,103
- Look, why don't we
 just say good night,

1077
00:57:55,103 --> 00:57:57,896
and go to bed and
 get some sleep?

1078
00:57:57,896 --> 00:57:59,103
Let's face it, we're
 both wrung out,

1079
00:57:59,103 --> 00:58:01,448
it's been a long week today.

1080
00:58:02,689 --> 00:58:05,862
- It ain't been
 my usual Thursday.

1081
00:58:05,862 --> 00:58:07,586
- Mine either, honey.

1082
00:58:12,275 --> 00:58:14,862
[wind blowing]

1083
00:59:02,034 --> 00:59:03,862
- Testing, testing.

1084
00:59:03,862 --> 00:59:05,931
Mary had a little lamb.

1085
00:59:05,931 --> 00:59:08,586
[tape rewinding]

1086
00:59:08,586 --> 00:59:11,034
- [Audrey] Sally,
 call Nettelston,

1087
00:59:11,034 --> 00:59:12,862
tell him not to
 finalize the deal yet.

1088
00:59:12,862 --> 00:59:15,206
It still doesn't
 sit right with me.

1089
00:59:15,206 --> 00:59:17,206
Call Phillip to check
 on the Hendrix stock,

1090
00:59:17,206 --> 00:59:18,413
it's making me nervous.

1091
00:59:18,413 --> 00:59:19,586
If you can't reach him--

1092
00:59:19,586 --> 00:59:21,448
- [Luanne] Testing, testing.

1093
00:59:21,448 --> 00:59:23,413
Mary had a little lamb.

1094
00:59:23,413 --> 00:59:26,655
[dramatic piano music]

1095
00:59:28,034 --> 00:59:29,586
Audrey?

1096
00:59:29,586 --> 00:59:31,517
This is me, Luanne.

1097
00:59:31,517 --> 00:59:34,344
This is to you
 that I can't do it.

1098
00:59:43,000 --> 00:59:45,758
This is one of the stupidest
 things I ever done in my life,

1099
00:59:45,758 --> 00:59:48,586
and I've done
 entertaining things.

1100
00:59:50,068 --> 00:59:51,793
I don't know whatever
 come into my mind

1101
00:59:51,793 --> 00:59:54,034
to think I could do it,

1102
00:59:54,034 --> 00:59:55,724
after all this time.

1103
00:59:56,862 --> 01:00:00,448
What would I say to him,
after all this time?

1104
01:00:00,448 --> 01:00:01,379
- [Voice On Intercom] Final call

1105
01:00:01,379 --> 01:00:03,000
for flight 901 to Little Rock,

1106
01:00:03,000 --> 01:00:05,000
boarding at gate number two.

1107
01:00:05,000 --> 01:00:06,413
- [Audrey voiceover] I
 know no one will think

1108
01:00:06,413 --> 01:00:09,551
too highly of me for chickening
out at the last minute,

1109
01:00:09,551 --> 01:00:14,551
but no one else is in
 my shoes so [muffled].

1110
01:00:23,931 --> 01:00:26,689
I'll pay you back for the
 expenses you went through.

1111
01:00:26,689 --> 01:00:28,241
It might take a while.

1112
01:00:28,241 --> 01:00:30,931
At least I'm paying
 my own way back.

1113
01:00:30,931 --> 01:00:33,413
I would have done that anyhow.

1114
01:00:36,586 --> 01:00:39,862
I'm sorry you went
 to so much trouble.

1115
01:00:39,862 --> 01:00:42,206
I don't blame you if
 you're really ticked off.

1116
01:00:42,206 --> 01:00:44,344
You really went to
 a lot of trouble.

1117
01:00:44,344 --> 01:00:46,448
You're a really good person,

1118
01:00:46,448 --> 01:00:47,758
but I wish I'd never
 laid eyes on you

1119
01:00:47,758 --> 01:00:49,724
if you know what I mean.

1120
01:00:51,724 --> 01:00:55,344
I hope your son's gonna
be okay, and have life.

1121
01:00:55,344 --> 01:00:57,310
Well, I guess that's all.

1122
01:01:32,517 --> 01:01:35,413
[doorbell ringing]

1123
01:01:45,931 --> 01:01:47,206
- I gotta do some shoppin'.

1124
01:01:47,206 --> 01:01:50,275
My clothes are flying
 to Little Rock.

1125
01:01:54,551 --> 01:01:55,344
- That,

1126
01:01:57,379 --> 01:01:58,206
or that?

1127
01:02:01,517 --> 01:02:02,344
No.

1128
01:02:16,586 --> 01:02:17,413
Hi.

1129
01:02:20,551 --> 01:02:22,413
Luanne, this is my son, James.

1130
01:02:22,413 --> 01:02:24,827
James, Luanne Barnes.

1131
01:02:24,827 --> 01:02:25,931
- Hi.

1132
01:02:25,931 --> 01:02:26,758
- Hello.

1133
01:02:26,758 --> 01:02:28,517
Thank you for coming.

1134
01:02:33,862 --> 01:02:35,241
Would you care for some
coffee or anything?

1135
01:02:35,241 --> 01:02:36,586
We can go to the cafeteria.

1136
01:02:36,586 --> 01:02:37,551
- I'm okay.

1137
01:02:37,551 --> 01:02:38,896
We had breakfast.

1138
01:02:38,896 --> 01:02:39,862
You?

1139
01:02:39,862 --> 01:02:40,758
- I'm fine.

1140
01:02:42,517 --> 01:02:44,758
Why don't we go on up then?

1141
01:02:59,379 --> 01:03:00,724
- Are you awake?

1142
01:03:02,241 --> 01:03:04,724
- The plane crashed,
there were no survivors.

1143
01:03:04,724 --> 01:03:07,931
I'm terribly sorry about Audrey.

1144
01:03:07,931 --> 01:03:09,000
- She's here.

1145
01:03:11,517 --> 01:03:14,034
- Can we discuss
 this for a few weeks?

1146
01:03:14,034 --> 01:03:16,206
- It's gonna be all right.

1147
01:03:17,551 --> 01:03:18,724
- Don't leave.

1148
01:03:20,551 --> 01:03:24,206
- You want to think
about that for a minute?

1149
01:03:44,655 --> 01:03:47,896
[sad orchestral music]

1150
01:04:08,793 --> 01:04:11,551
- What's wrong
 with this picture?

1151
01:04:21,724 --> 01:04:23,551
- How ya been, Donnie?

1152
01:04:25,862 --> 01:04:29,586
I guess that's
 startin' out stupid.

1153
01:04:29,586 --> 01:04:33,586
- I've been fine prior
 to this current nuisance.

1154
01:04:35,793 --> 01:04:38,068
I like your outfit.

1155
01:04:38,068 --> 01:04:39,241
Tres chic, ma.

1156
01:04:40,344 --> 01:04:42,000
- You kiddin'? It's Audrey's.

1157
01:04:42,000 --> 01:04:43,275
It's a long story.

1158
01:04:43,275 --> 01:04:46,655
Not that I don't have
some nice things myself.

1159
01:04:46,655 --> 01:04:48,931
But, it's too tight though.

1160
01:04:50,137 --> 01:04:52,310
I got to do some shoppin'.

1161
01:04:54,413 --> 01:04:57,379
- Would you like to sit down?

1162
01:04:57,379 --> 01:04:59,206
Or do you have to run?

1163
01:05:02,344 --> 01:05:03,344
I'm kidding.

1164
01:05:13,586 --> 01:05:14,862
- Been a while.

1165
01:05:16,344 --> 01:05:19,344
- You haven't changed a bit.

1166
01:05:19,344 --> 01:05:21,896
You're looking very well.

1167
01:05:21,896 --> 01:05:24,758
- Yeah well, don't
 let the hair fool ya.

1168
01:05:24,758 --> 01:05:25,827
It comes off.

1169
01:05:27,172 --> 01:05:28,931
- It's very becoming.

1170
01:05:31,448 --> 01:05:34,103
- You got no accent anymore.

1171
01:05:34,103 --> 01:05:34,965
- No.

1172
01:05:36,206 --> 01:05:38,758
- Well maybe a little
smidgen here and there.

1173
01:05:38,758 --> 01:05:40,655
You can hardly hear it.

1174
01:05:48,551 --> 01:05:51,517
Hear you got real successful?

1175
01:05:51,517 --> 01:05:53,931
- Yes, I've done pretty well.

1176
01:05:56,551 --> 01:05:59,068
Would you care for a chocolate?

1177
01:06:00,655 --> 01:06:01,655
- No thanks.

1178
01:06:08,206 --> 01:06:10,482
From drawing, more or less?

1179
01:06:11,344 --> 01:06:12,344
- I'm sorry.

1180
01:06:13,655 --> 01:06:17,379
- I mean you got successful
 just from drawing?

1181
01:06:19,172 --> 01:06:20,448
- More or less.

1182
01:06:25,827 --> 01:06:28,896
- You was always
 drawing as a kid.

1183
01:06:28,896 --> 01:06:32,551
Some kids draw and
 come to nothing but,

1184
01:06:32,551 --> 01:06:35,137
you was always real good at it.

1185
01:06:36,517 --> 01:06:39,068
- You taped them on the fridge.

1186
01:06:41,793 --> 01:06:42,620
- Yeah.

1187
01:06:52,448 --> 01:06:54,103
Can I smoke in here?

1188
01:06:57,896 --> 01:07:00,103
- He wants to go home.

1189
01:07:00,103 --> 01:07:02,275
- I thought the
 two of you agreed?

1190
01:07:02,275 --> 01:07:03,758
- He's reneged.

1191
01:07:03,758 --> 01:07:05,172
- Are you gonna let him?

1192
01:07:05,172 --> 01:07:06,689
- Yes.

1193
01:07:06,689 --> 01:07:08,586
- Is that a good idea?

1194
01:07:08,586 --> 01:07:10,689
- It is for him.

1195
01:07:10,689 --> 01:07:11,827
In his place I'd
 want to be allowed

1196
01:07:11,827 --> 01:07:14,000
to do what I wanted to do.

1197
01:07:19,000 --> 01:07:22,310
[siren in the distance]

1198
01:07:26,137 --> 01:07:28,655
- I have to ask you something.

1199
01:07:31,620 --> 01:07:33,965
Why haven't you been tested?

1200
01:07:37,620 --> 01:07:39,103
- I don't want to.

1201
01:07:40,413 --> 01:07:42,000
- Is that wise?

1202
01:07:42,000 --> 01:07:44,137
- Wisdom beyond my
 years I like to think.

1203
01:07:44,137 --> 01:07:45,344
- James?

1204
01:07:45,344 --> 01:07:48,586
- If I don't have it,
 it doesn't matter.

1205
01:07:50,724 --> 01:07:51,551
If I do,

1206
01:07:55,758 --> 01:07:56,724
and I said to you
 a few days ago,

1207
01:07:56,724 --> 01:07:59,068
we know what we want to know.

1208
01:07:59,068 --> 01:08:01,448
- That was about me.

1209
01:08:01,448 --> 01:08:03,000
- This is about me.

1210
01:08:07,206 --> 01:08:10,689
- Did they tell you
 you're in no danger?

1211
01:08:10,689 --> 01:08:12,275
James and Audrey?

1212
01:08:12,275 --> 01:08:13,793
- About what?

1213
01:08:13,793 --> 01:08:15,206
- Me.

1214
01:08:15,206 --> 01:08:16,034
This.

1215
01:08:18,310 --> 01:08:20,793
- Yeah, they told me.

1216
01:08:20,793 --> 01:08:22,551
- Sure you don't,

1217
01:08:22,551 --> 01:08:23,379
really,

1218
01:08:25,275 --> 01:08:27,344
you can have a chocolate.

1219
01:08:28,586 --> 01:08:30,620
- This ain't easy
 for me, you know.

1220
01:08:30,620 --> 01:08:32,862
I just want to be
 upfront about it.

1221
01:08:32,862 --> 01:08:34,206
- Thank you for coming.

1222
01:08:34,206 --> 01:08:35,034
- You mean it?

1223
01:08:35,034 --> 01:08:35,896
- Mean it.

1224
01:08:36,862 --> 01:08:38,172
- I wasn't sure.

1225
01:08:39,448 --> 01:08:42,103
All I've been thinking
 about since yesterday,

1226
01:08:42,103 --> 01:08:44,448
is if I wanted to come,

1227
01:08:44,448 --> 01:08:46,655
until this morning,
 I started wondering,

1228
01:08:46,655 --> 01:08:49,034
what your position
 was on the situation.

1229
01:08:49,034 --> 01:08:51,586
- That's my position.

1230
01:08:51,586 --> 01:08:53,482
- I'm sorry what
happened to you, Donnie.

1231
01:08:53,482 --> 01:08:55,034
- We said soon is mended.

1232
01:08:55,034 --> 01:08:59,103
- But you brought it on
yourself, didn't you?

1233
01:08:59,103 --> 01:09:00,000
Didn't you?

1234
01:09:02,103 --> 01:09:02,965
I'm sorry.

1235
01:09:02,965 --> 01:09:04,517
I didn't mean to shout.

1236
01:09:04,517 --> 01:09:05,931
It just come out.

1237
01:09:13,206 --> 01:09:14,620
- Arms restored,

1238
01:09:14,620 --> 01:09:16,965
these are such trying times.

1239
01:09:19,310 --> 01:09:21,758
- Is someone smoking in here?

1240
01:09:22,896 --> 01:09:26,068
- To whose health
 would it be hazardous?

1241
01:09:32,689 --> 01:09:35,103
How do you like Audrey?

1242
01:09:35,103 --> 01:09:37,689
- Boy, she's something
 else isn't she?

1243
01:09:37,689 --> 01:09:39,862
You know she's got me
 staying at her house?

1244
01:09:39,862 --> 01:09:41,103
Did you know that?

1245
01:09:41,103 --> 01:09:42,724
- That's very nice.

1246
01:09:45,379 --> 01:09:48,103
- You know she said that

1247
01:09:48,103 --> 01:09:51,000
what do you say,
you designed it?

1248
01:09:51,000 --> 01:09:52,482
It's real nice.

1249
01:09:52,482 --> 01:09:53,310
Real nice.

1250
01:09:56,965 --> 01:09:59,000
You know what I'd love to do?

1251
01:09:59,000 --> 01:10:01,275
I would really love

1252
01:10:01,275 --> 01:10:04,620
to take a swim in
 her swimming pool.

1253
01:10:04,620 --> 01:10:07,896
Doesn't anybody ever
 swim in them pools?

1254
01:10:07,896 --> 01:10:09,034
You know, in the movies,

1255
01:10:09,034 --> 01:10:11,620
nobody ever swims in them.

1256
01:10:11,620 --> 01:10:13,206
They're just there.

1257
01:10:14,758 --> 01:10:16,586
- Take the plunge, ma.

1258
01:10:22,275 --> 01:10:25,551
- There's something
 I want to show you.

1259
01:10:37,034 --> 01:10:38,172
Remember this?

1260
01:10:50,103 --> 01:10:52,655
Remember when you drew that up?

1261
01:10:53,862 --> 01:10:57,482
You was about, I don't
 know, eight or nine.

1262
01:10:57,482 --> 01:11:01,862
You said you was gonna
 build that for me, some day.

1263
01:11:01,862 --> 01:11:02,689
For us.

1264
01:11:04,620 --> 01:11:05,862
A magic castle.

1265
01:11:08,344 --> 01:11:11,793
And we'd live in it
 together, you and me.

1266
01:11:16,448 --> 01:11:18,965
And it would be full of magic.

1267
01:11:27,206 --> 01:11:29,310
Your son's real good-lookin'.

1268
01:11:29,310 --> 01:11:30,655
- Yes, isn't he?

1269
01:11:32,068 --> 01:11:33,241
- Could have really been
 something with the ladies,

1270
01:11:33,241 --> 01:11:34,241
couldn't he?

1271
01:11:35,448 --> 01:11:39,068
His father must have
 been real handsome.

1272
01:11:39,068 --> 01:11:40,551
Oh I mean, I didn't
 mean it that way,

1273
01:11:40,551 --> 01:11:42,862
I mean that you are a
very good-lookin' woman.

1274
01:11:42,862 --> 01:11:45,379
- His father was a real looker.

1275
01:11:47,206 --> 01:11:49,896
- You got a boyfriend?

1276
01:11:49,896 --> 01:11:51,310
- No.

1277
01:11:51,310 --> 01:11:53,827
- Me neither, lately.

1278
01:11:53,827 --> 01:11:55,620
It's a bitch ain't it?

1279
01:11:59,379 --> 01:12:02,000
- How did it go with Donald?

1280
01:12:02,000 --> 01:12:04,310
- I hardly recognized him.

1281
01:12:04,310 --> 01:12:06,965
He never was too
 hardy, built-wise.

1282
01:12:06,965 --> 01:12:09,620
Took more after me
 than his old man.

1283
01:12:09,620 --> 01:12:12,655
Freddy was a real big fella.

1284
01:12:12,655 --> 01:12:16,758
Of course, he didn't believe
 that he was his old man.

1285
01:12:16,758 --> 01:12:17,689
- Donald didn't?

1286
01:12:17,689 --> 01:12:19,344
- No, Freddy.

1287
01:12:19,344 --> 01:12:21,862
Didn't believe
 Donnie was his son.

1288
01:12:21,862 --> 01:12:24,517
Said there was no way
 that any son of his,

1289
01:12:24,517 --> 01:12:26,241
could be one of them.

1290
01:12:27,551 --> 01:12:29,000
- That's insane.

1291
01:12:29,000 --> 01:12:32,620
- Yeah, well even I knew
 that was a bit far-fetched.

1292
01:12:32,620 --> 01:12:34,551
Still in all, I sure
 didn't like having to take

1293
01:12:34,551 --> 01:12:37,413
a rap like that on
 account of Donnie.

1294
01:12:37,413 --> 01:12:39,034
There's one thing nobody can say

1295
01:12:39,034 --> 01:12:41,827
about me is I fooled around.

1296
01:12:41,827 --> 01:12:44,275
I'd take 'em as they come,
 but I take 'em one at a time.

1297
01:12:44,275 --> 01:12:46,068
- You didn't take a rap
on account of Donnie,

1298
01:12:46,068 --> 01:12:47,862
you took it on account
 of your husband.

1299
01:12:47,862 --> 01:12:49,413
- Ah, either way.

1300
01:12:49,413 --> 01:12:50,724
- No, it isn't either way.

1301
01:12:50,724 --> 01:12:52,689
Don't you understand
 the difference?

1302
01:12:52,689 --> 01:12:56,758
- I sure do tend to get you
 all stressed out, don't I?

1303
01:12:56,758 --> 01:12:58,758
